{
  "texts": [
    "This is achieved by representing molecular structures as string notations, such as the Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry Systems (SMILES 14, Fig. 1a), among others 15, 16.",
    "These molecular strings are then used for model training and subsequent generation of molecules in textual form.",
    "Compared to generative methods based on molecular graphs 17, CLMs can learn more complex molecular properties better 8, and generate increasingly larger molecules more efficiently 18, 19.",
    "These aspects have made CLMs become one of the de facto approaches for de novo drug design.",
    "Several CLM architectures have been proposed for de novo design 20, the most popular of which are long short-term memory (LSTM) [3] [4] [5] 21, 22 models."
  ]
}